President Donald J. Trump recently held a meeting with several officials, including Attorney General Sessions and Secretary Nielsen, to discuss efforts to enhance the security of the country's election systems. The administration aims to collaborate with state and local election officials to ensure the integrity of every American's vote. The President was briefed on ongoing federal efforts, such as information sharing, best practices like using paper ballots, security clearances, and security assessments. Trump emphasized the connection between election security and national security and pledged continued support to state and local governments in securing their election processes.